This is the protocol for a review and there is no abstract. The objectives are as follows:, Primary objective: To quantify the decrease in systolic blood pressure (SBP) and diastolic blood pressure (DBP) of specific combinations of drugs versus the individual drugs in patients with elevated blood pressure., Secondary objectives:, 1.To determine the effects of specific combinations of drugs on variability of blood pressure., 2.To determine the effects of specific combinations of drugs on pulse pressure., 3.To quantify the effect of specific combinations of drugs on heart rate., 4.To quantify the effect of specific combinations of drugs on withdrawals due to adverse events